27/02/2011
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The Court of BiH announced on Friday (February 25th) it has confirmed charges against Montenegrin citizen Veselin Vlahovic, known as the "monster of Grbavica", who is accused of war crimes committed against Bosniaks and Croats in Sarajevo in 1992 and 1993. As a member of a paramilitary group, Vlahovic allegedly took part in murders, rapes, illegal detention and torture of non-Serb civilians. Prosecutors submitted the charges on February 19th. (Hayat, Radio Free Europe, RTCG - 25/02/11)
